news.Title: Two dead, one injured in recent spate of child shootings in Houston
news.item: Two children are dead and one is critically injured in the Houston area in three separate shootings over the span of four days.

news.Title: Jameis Winston files to trademark namesake
news.item: Potential No. 1 NFL draft pick Jameis Winston is already looking for more dollars than his signing bonus will carry.

news.Title: Houston Texans to trade or release Andre Johnson
news.item: After learning he would have a reduced role next season, Andre Johnson requested to be traded or released from the Houston Texans, according to John McClain.

news.Title: Washington Nationals sign Tony Gwynn Jr.
news.item: A legendary baseball name has been invited to the Washington Nationals spring training camp.

news.Title: Dallas Cowboys' Murray on track for free agency
news.item: All-Pro running back DeMarco Murray appears to have run through the end zone and into the open market.

news.Title: PGA denies rumor that Tiger Woods was banned from tour
news.item: The PGA denied rumors Monday that Tiger Woods was suspended from the tour for failing a drug test.

news.Title: Former Red Sox pitcher Curt Schilling calls out daughter's cyberbullies
news.item: Former Red Sox pitcher Curt Schilling called out several Twitter users for posting 'vulgar and defiling' tweets about his daughter Gabby.

news.Title: Dr. Ben Carson eyes presidential nomination with exploratory committee
news.item: Conservative physician and author Ben Carson launched a presidential exploratory committee Tuesday, taking another step toward a bid for the GOP nomination.

news.Title: Former D.C. cabbie detained in Somalia on terror charges
news.item: A former Washington, D.C.-area taxi driver who was on the FBI's Most Wanted Terrorists list was detained by the Somalian government.

news.Title: Jury deciding between life, death for convicted killer Jodi Arias
news.item: A jury is deciding between life in prison or the death sentence for Jodi Arias, convicted in 2013 of killing her boyfriend.

news.Title: Tsarnaev attorneys ask for fourth time to move Boston Marathon bombing trial
news.item: Attorneys for Boston Marathon bombing suspect Dzhokhar Tsarnaev asked a judge for the fourth time to stop jury selection and move the trial somewhere else.

news.Title: Los Angeles police chief says man killed on Skid Row tried to grab cop's gun
news.item: The homeless man killed by police in Los Angeles' Skid Row neighborhood 'forcibly grabbed' for an officer's gun, Los Angeles Police Chief Charlie Beck said.

news.Title: Warren Buffett: Elizabeth Warren is too 'angry'
news.item: Warren Buffett, one of the world's richest men, says Sen. Elizabeth Warren's criticism of Wall Street is too aggressive.

news.Title: Georgia postpones execution of female death row inmate over drug concerns
news.item: The planned execution of Georgia inmate Kelly Gissendaner was postponed Monday over concerns about the lethal injection drugs.

news.Title: Hillary Clinton only used personal email account for State Department business
news.item: Hillary Clinton only used a personal email account to conduct official business while serving as U.S. secretary of state, the State Department confirmed Monday.

news.Title: Two dead, one injured in recent spate of child shootings in Houston
news.item: Two children are dead and one is critically injured in the Houston area in three separate shootings over the span of four days.

news.Title: Tense U.S.-Russia meeting over Ukrainian cease-fire
news.item: Secretary of State John Kerry and Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov met in Geneva to discuss the shaky cease-fire in Ukraine.

news.Title: North Korean envoy: Regime can launch preemptive strikes
news.item: North Korea's top foreign envoy said at a United Nations-backed disarmament conference that his country has the capability to deter the United States and launch preemptive strikes if necessary.

news.Title: Twitter employees, co-founder threatened by IS
news.item: Twitter is investigating alleged death threats by the Islamic State on the company's co-founder Jack Dorsey and its employees.
